      "date": "2022-12-10 19:24:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nNote that we are currently testing with ppc64le (little endian), and not ppc (big endian), so I'm not sure this patch is doing the right thing?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "03f94a61352de77c0df8d579c373ede7101a78d2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2022-12-10 19:29:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nI checked the test results, and ppc64le is already running these tests without problems, so I don't think this patch is needed until there is some sign that ppc64 is actually passing (which we are unable to test in our current environment).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "5848d930c3155c3badb61d705d3ef0c0292e49a2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2022-12-10 19:44:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI looked at the ticket and it never pointed out it was an issue only with big endian systems. Is this true for ARM as well?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "bcca7bc3d886652040d029b3a01131868d5eccac",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2022-12-11 00:27:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> I looked at the ticket and it never pointed out it was an issue only with big endian systems. Is this true for ARM as well?\n\nAt the time this was filed, PPC was only tuning bug endian. I think our ARM testing has always been little endian, but with 64KB PAGE_SIZE. PPC also uses 64KB PAGE_SIZE, but the endian conversion in Lustre is really rusty these days from disuse.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "3b896943381c149c671dfdae198b64053bb1079a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2022-12-13 02:06:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHi Xilang. I included on this ticket since it involves issues with big endian systems. Do you test Lustre with big endian ARM systems?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "2042123a1f1a8d4f488f4e5f406142505c069314",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 887,
        "name": "xinliang",
        "email": "xinliang.liu@linaro.org",
        "username": "xinliang.liu"
      },
      "date": "2022-12-13 02:40:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> Hi Xilang. I included on this ticket since it involves issues with big endian systems. Do you test Lustre with big endian ARM systems?\n\nSorry, James, I have no big-endian ARM systems in hand.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
